<subSubSection id="C3531CF20178A45FA2076FC234ECFC64" box="[312,1248,942,969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF64F790178A45FA2076FC234ECFC64" blockId="8.[264,1323,862,1889]" box="[312,1248,942,969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA2076FC231BBFC65" bold="true" box="[312,439,942,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0178A45FA2806FC33206FC65" box="[447,522,943,968]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA2806FC33206FC65" box="[447,522,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Tethya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
orange, with tylasters and completely microspined oxyasters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3531CF20178A45FA2076FBA3153F9E4" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF64F790178A45FA2076FBA324EFB3C" blockId="8.[264,1323,862,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA2076FBA31DCFC5D" bold="true" box="[312,464,982,1008]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description.</emphasis>
Body hemispherical, 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA1E86FBB3324FC5C" box="[727,808,983,1009]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter by 1.0 cm high (
<figureCitation id="137253FC0178A45FA7B56FBB34DDFC5C" box="[1162,1233,983,1009]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[264,367,974,998]" captionTargetBox="[285,1296,317,944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[272,1315,309,966]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. In situ close­ups of three species of Tethya from Abrolhos Archipelago, Brazil. A, B, Tethya brasiliana sp. nov. (paratypes); C, Tethya ignis sp. nov. (holotype); D, Tethya rubra sp. nov. (holotype)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169080/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA7FD6FBB34DDFC5C" box="[1218,1233,983,1009]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C, 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA7CA6FBB3508FC5C" box="[1269,1284,983,1009]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
A). Colour in life orange; cortex white or yellow and choanosome yellowish brown in alcohol. Surface smooth or with flattened tubercles separated by up to 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA0DB684B3420FBEC" box="[996,1068,1063,1089]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
. The surface between adjacent tubercles is reticulated. Buds attached to sponge surface. Oscules not visible. Cortex firm, choanosome soft.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF64F790178A45FA20768F33336FA9C" blockId="8.[264,1323,862,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA20768F3320DFB15" box="[312,513,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cortical skeleton</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="137253FC0178A45FA12D68F33255FB14" box="[530,601,1183,1209]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[264,367,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[311,1273,616,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,604,1756]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Tethya ignis sp. nov. A, preserved holotype (MNRJ 5322 A); B, architecture of the ectosome and choanosome; C, strongyloxea; D, spheraster; E, oxyaster and tylaster; F, oxyaster. B – C, LM; D – F, SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169083/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA17568F33255FB14" box="[586,601,1183,1209]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Cortical layer 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA01168F333EEFB14" box="[814,994,1183,1209]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="1500.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="1000.0">1000–2000 m</quantity>
thick. Spherasters scattered in the cortex. Tylasters especially abundant in the surface, forming a dermal crust. Occasionally, some megascleres project beyond the surface. Regular cavities, 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA74D68833506FAA4" box="[1138,1290,1263,1289]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="550.0" valueMax="800.0" valueMin="300.0">300–800 m</quantity>
in diameter, located between megascleres bundles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF64F790178A45FA20769533349FA2C" blockId="8.[264,1323,862,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA20769533240FAF5" box="[312,588,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Choanosomal skeleton</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="137253FC0178A45FA15A695332B8FAF4" box="[613,692,1343,1369]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[264,367,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[311,1273,616,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,604,1756]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Tethya ignis sp. nov. A, preserved holotype (MNRJ 5322 A); B, architecture of the ectosome and choanosome; C, strongyloxea; D, spheraster; E, oxyaster and tylaster; F, oxyaster. B – C, LM; D – F, SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169083/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA19A695332B8FAF4" box="[677,692,1343,1369]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Tylasters abundant in the upper choanosome. Spherasters rare, located near the cortical region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF64F790178A45FA20769E33153F9E4" blockId="8.[264,1323,862,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA20769E33196FA05" box="[312,410,1423,1448]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Spicules</emphasis>
. Main strongyloxeas 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA1A569E3330CFA04" box="[666,768,1423,1449]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="710.0" valueMax="816.0" valueMin="604.0">604–816</number>
– 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA02F69E3338EFA04" box="[784,898,1423,1449]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.063" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="1.063">1.063 m</quantity>
long by 
<date id="FFF769B90178A45FA0D369E3346DFA04" box="[1004,1121,1423,1449]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1914-10-21">
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA0D369E33439FA04" box="[1004,1077,1423,1449]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="12.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="10.0">10–14</number>
– 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA77A69E3346DFA04" box="[1093,1121,1423,1449]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="21.0">21</quantity>
</date>
m wide (n= 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA63C69E3352EFA04" box="[1283,1314,1423,1449]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="30.0">30</number>
) (
<figureCitation id="137253FC0178A45FA22E69DB3154FA7C" box="[273,344,1463,1489]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[264,367,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[311,1273,616,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,604,1756]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Tethya ignis sp. nov. A, preserved holotype (MNRJ 5322 A); B, architecture of the ectosome and choanosome; C, strongyloxea; D, spheraster; E, oxyaster and tylaster; F, oxyaster. B – C, LM; D – F, SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169083/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA27669DB3154FA7C" box="[329,344,1463,1489]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Accessory strongyloxeas 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA18C69DB3315FA7C" box="[691,793,1463,1489]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="367.0" valueMax="432.0" valueMin="302.0">302–432</number>
– 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA01669DB3389FA7C" box="[809,901,1463,1489]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.66" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="566.0">566 m</quantity>
by 
<date id="FFF769B90178A45FA08B69DB3406FA7C" box="[948,1034,1463,1489]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1911-08-05">
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA08B69DB33D2FA7C" box="[948,990,1463,1489]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8</number>
– 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA0D169DB3406FA7C" box="[1006,1034,1463,1489]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="11.0">11</quantity>
</date>
m (n= 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA75169DB3482FA7C" box="[1134,1166,1463,1489]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="30.0">30</number>
). Spherasters 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA23769B3315DFA54" box="[264,337,1503,1529]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="41.0" valueMax="53.0" valueMin="29.0">29–53</number>
– 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA25E69B331A1FA54" box="[353,429,1503,1529]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="68.0">68 m</quantity>
(n= 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA2E169B331F2FA54" box="[478,510,1503,1529]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="20.0">20</number>
), R/C = 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA15D69B3328BFA54" box="[610,647,1503,1529]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="0.5">0.5</number>
–1.0 (
<figureCitation id="137253FC0178A45FA1F469B3331DFA54" box="[715,785,1503,1529]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[264,367,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[311,1273,616,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,604,1756]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Tethya ignis sp. nov. A, preserved holotype (MNRJ 5322 A); B, architecture of the ectosome and choanosome; C, strongyloxea; D, spheraster; E, oxyaster and tylaster; F, oxyaster. B – C, LM; D – F, SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169083/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA03D69B3331DFA54" box="[770,785,1503,1529]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Completely microspined oxyasters 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA7E269B33527FA54" box="[1245,1323,1503,1529]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="25.0">25 m</quantity>
in diameter (
<figureCitation id="137253FC0178A45FA2906A6B31F4F98C" box="[431,504,1543,1569]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[264,367,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[311,1273,616,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,604,1756]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Tethya ignis sp. nov. A, preserved holotype (MNRJ 5322 A); B, architecture of the ectosome and choanosome; C, strongyloxea; D, spheraster; E, oxyaster and tylaster; F, oxyaster. B – C, LM; D – F, SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169083/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA2D56A6B31F4F98C" box="[490,504,1543,1569]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
E–F). Tylasters (
<figureCitation id="137253FC0178A45FA1F26A6B331AF98C" box="[717,790,1543,1569]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[264,367,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[311,1273,616,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,604,1756]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Tethya ignis sp. nov. A, preserved holotype (MNRJ 5322 A); B, architecture of the ectosome and choanosome; C, strongyloxea; D, spheraster; E, oxyaster and tylaster; F, oxyaster. B – C, LM; D – F, SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169083/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA0376A6B331AF98C" box="[776,790,1543,1569]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
E) generally with short rays, 
<date id="FFF769B90178A45FA7426A6B34FDF98C" box="[1149,1265,1543,1569]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1913-10-18">
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA7426A6B34C9F98C" box="[1149,1221,1543,1569]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13</number>
– 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0178A45FA7E96A6B34FDF98C" box="[1238,1265,1543,1569]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="18.0">18</quantity>
</date>
mm (n= 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA20C6A43315DF9E4" box="[307,337,1583,1609]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="10.0">10</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3531CF20178A45FA2076A3A32E8F944" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF64F790178A45FA2076A3A32E8F944" blockId="8.[264,1323,862,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA2076A3A3279F9DD" bold="true" box="[312,629,1622,1648]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
Endemic from Abrolhos Archipelago, Bahia state, 
<collectingCountry id="F35E0FE90178A45FA7E36A3B352BF9DC" box="[1244,1319,1623,1649]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, found only in Redonda Island. This species occurs in the intertidal zone and was found on the underside of boulders. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0178A45FA1766ACB32D4F96D" box="[585,728,1703,1728]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ignis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA1766ACB32D4F96D" box="[585,728,1703,1728]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Tethya ignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA1DD6ACA334DF96D" bold="true" box="[738,833,1702,1728]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E2E100178A45FA1DD6ACA334DF96D" box="[738,833,1702,1728]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very rare, and only a single specimen has been found despite extensive search.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3531CF20178A45FA2076A9A3506F8BC" box="[312,1290,1782,1809]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF64F790178A45FA2076A9A3506F8BC" blockId="8.[264,1323,862,1889]" box="[312,1290,1782,1809]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA2076A9A31C8F8BD" bold="true" box="[312,452,1782,1808]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0178A45FA1786A9B328CF8BD" box="[583,640,1783,1808]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ignis">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA1786A9B328CF8BD" box="[583,640,1783,1808]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">ignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the orange external colour of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3531CF20178A45EA2076B7234F6FE50" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF64F790178A45EA2076B7234F6FE50" blockId="8.[264,1323,862,1889]" lastBlockId="9.[264,1323,284,510]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA2076B7231BDF895" bold="true" box="[312,433,1822,1848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA2866B733354F895" box="[441,856,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0178A45FA2866B73325CF895" box="[441,592,1823,1848]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ovum">Tethya ovum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0178A45FA1626B7332B4F895" box="[605,696,1823,1848]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ensis">T. ensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0178A45FA1FA6B733354F895" authority="Bowerbank, 1872 (Sara et al. 1992)" authorityName="Bowerbank, 1872 (Sara et al." authorityYear="1992" box="[709,856,1823,1848]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="norvegica">T. norvegica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD832880178A45FA05F6B73343DF894" author="Bowerbank" box="[864,1073,1823,1849]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Bowerbank, J. S. (1872) Contributions to a general history of the Spongidae. I - III. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 115 - 129, 196 - 202, 626 - 635." type="proceedings paper" year="1872">
Bowerbank, 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA0C96B73343DF894" box="[1014,1073,1823,1849]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1872.0">1872</number>
</bibRefCitation>
(Sarà et al. 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA7FE6B7334F3F894" box="[1217,1279,1823,1849]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1992.0">1992</number>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0178A45FA62A6B733236F8CC" authority="Sara et al., 2000" authorityName="Sara et al." authorityYear="2000" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA62A6B73315AF8CD" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">T. ornata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD832880178A45FA25A6B2B3236F8CC" author="Sara" box="[357,570,1863,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="16" refString="Sara, M., Bavestrello, G. &amp; Calcinai, B. (2000) New Tethya species (Porifera, Demospongiae) from the Pacific area. Zoosystema, 22 (2), 345 - 353." type="journal article" year="2000">
Sarà et al., 
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA2C06B2B3236F8CC" box="[511,570,1863,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0178A45FA1BD6B2B3371F8CD" box="[642,893,1863,1888]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="subSpecies" species="diploderma" subSpecies="sensu">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA1BD6B2B3371F8CD" box="[642,893,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">T. diploderma sensu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD832880178A45FA0886B2B349AF8CC" author="Laubenfels" box="[951,1174,1863,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Laubenfels, M. W. de (1953) Sponges of the Gulf of Mexico. Bulletin of Marine Science of the Gulf and Caribbean, 2 (3), 511 - 557." type="journal article" year="1953">
Laubenfels (
<number id="3D815D5E0178A45FA76F6B2B3481F8CC" box="[1104,1165,1863,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1953.0">1953</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
(
<emphasis id="B93D936B0178A45FA7916B2B3526F8CD" box="[1198,1322,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">non sensu</emphasis>
Schmidt) are similar because they all have completely spined asters. They differ however from the new species in other characters: 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0179A45EA02D6D2833AAFEF0" box="[786,934,324,349]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ensis">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0179A45EA02D6D2833AAFEF0" box="[786,934,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tethya ensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0179A45EA0D66D283446FEF0" box="[1001,1098,324,349]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ovum">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0179A45EA0D66D283446FEF0" box="[1001,1098,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. ovum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have microspined tylasters instead of oxyasters; 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0179A45EA1496D003317FE28" box="[630,795,364,389]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0179A45EA1496D003317FE28" box="[630,795,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tethya ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has completely microspined strongylasters; 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0179A45EA2376DF831DDFE00" box="[264,465,404,429]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="norvegica">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0179A45EA2376DF831DDFE00" box="[264,465,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tethya norvegica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has micrasters with conical rays (similar to spherasters, 
<quantity id="4CB1E29C0179A45EA7576DF834B8FE03" box="[1128,1204,404,430]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="10.0">10 m</quantity>
in diameter), absent in the new species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0179A45EA14A6DD03395FE78" box="[629,921,444,469]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Porifera" rank="subSpecies" species="diploderma" subSpecies="sensu">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0179A45EA14A6DD03395FE78" box="[629,921,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tethya diploderma sensu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD832880179A45EA0FC6DD0348BFE7B" author="Laubenfels" box="[963,1159,444,470]" pageId="9" pageNumber="15" refString="Laubenfels, M. W. de (1953) Sponges of the Gulf of Mexico. Bulletin of Marine Science of the Gulf and Caribbean, 2 (3), 511 - 557." type="journal article" year="1953">
Laubenfels 
<number id="3D815D5E0179A45EA7736DD0348BFE7B" box="[1100,1159,444,470]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1953.0">1953</number>
</bibRefCitation>
has oxyasters with smooth or microspined, bifurcated rays, which are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4934FA0179A45EA7376D88349AFE50" box="[1032,1174,484,509]" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ignis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93D936B0179A45EA7376D88349AFE50" box="[1032,1174,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tethya ignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93D936B0179A45EA7A26D8F34F6FE50" bold="true" box="[1181,1274,483,509]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E2E100179A45EA7A26D8F34F6FE50" box="[1181,1274,483,509]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
